    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you on avoiding generalizations, but i've been reading some discussions online and even seeing some old studies that suggest there might be certain trends, like some groups being naturally more explosive or having different endurance profiles. if i'm trying to get the best results for my clients, wouldn't it be more practical to at least look at the statistical trends or common genetic predispositions that pop up in certain populations, even if it's not a hard rule for everyone?",
