    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "fair enough, i get the point about individualization. but i'm also curious about the actual science behind why those old studies even existed in the first place. like, is there any legitimate physiological basis for why certain populations might exhibit higher rates of specific traits, like fast-twitch vs slow-twitch dominance, or are those observations just completely debunked? i just want to know if there's any nuance there that i'm missing before i totally dismiss it.",
